<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675629>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Photographs of Macrochlamys leggeae sp. nov. and four other species in the genus Macrochlamys: (a) Macrochlamys leggeae sp. nov. (holotype) (NZSI M.31208/8); (b) Macrochlamys vesicula (Benson, 1838) (NZSI M.24473/5); (c) Macrochlamys glauca (Pfeiffer, 1846) (NZSI M.12954/2); (d) Macrochlamys kuluensis Blanford, 1904 (NZSI M.3704/1); (e) Macrochlamys nuda (Pfeiffer, 1852) (NZSI M.12923/2)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3675629/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675635>
    dc:description "Figure 5. The type localities of Macrochlamys species and the distributional range of Macrochlamys leggeae sp. nov. in western Himalaya of India." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3675635/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675639>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Scanning electron microscope images of the radula and jaw of Macrochlamys leggeae sp. nov (paratype NZSI M.31209/8): (a‒f) radula structure, (g) jaw of Macrochlamys leggeae sp. nov. (paratype NZSI M.31209/8)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3675639/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675641>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Genitalia of Macrochlamys leggeae sp. nov. (paratype, NZSI M.31209/8); at – atrium, ag – albumen gland, da – dart apparatus, drm – dart retractor muscle, e – epiphallus, epc – epiphallic caecum, fl – flagellum, fo – free oviduct, gd – gametolytic duct, gs – gametolytic sac, hd – hermaphrodite duct, ov – oviduct, p – penis, pc – penial caecum, pg – prostate gland, prm – penial retractor muscle, v – vagina, vd – vas deferens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3675641/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675633>
    dc:description "Figure 4. (a,b) Field photographs of Macrochlamys leggeae sp. nov. (c) Hilly grassland and valley above the Pushpawati River, type habitat of Macrochlamys leggeae sp. nov. (d) Extended view of valley of type habitat. (e,f) The peculiar habitat of type specimen at Valley of Flowers National Park, District Chamoli, Uttarakhand, India." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3675633/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675637>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Plot of components 1 and 2 resulting from the principal component analysis (PCA) of Macrochlamys leggeae sp. nov. (ML), Macrochlamys vesicula (MV), Macrochlamys glauca (MG), Macrochlamys kuluensis (MK) and Macrochlamys nuda (MN). The cluster direction and magnitude of the vectors reflect the degree of contribution by the shell ratio used in the analysis. Shell ratio: SL/ SW: shell length/shell width; AH/AW: aperture height/aperture width; AW/SH: aperture width/spire height; HBW/AH: height of the body whorl/aperture height; HBW/SH: height of the body whorl/spire height." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3675637/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

